        title: "Mistake 2: Treating AI as an IT project",
        content: `AI adoption fails when it is handed to the technology team and treated as a technical implementation project.
Technology teams are essential in AI adoption — but they are not the right people to lead it. The decisions that determine whether AI creates value are business decisions. Which process to automate. What success looks like. How the change will be communicated to the team. What the ROI case is. These are strategy and operations questions, not engineering questions.
When AI is led by IT, it tends to produce technically functional solutions to problems nobody asked to solve. When it is led by business operations — with technology in a supporting role — it produces things that actually change how work gets done.
The most effective AI implementations we work on at Aventra³ are led by a business owner, operations director or managing partner who understands the business problem deeply and treats technology as the tool rather than the answer.`
